HEADWORD: Calade
<hw>Ca*lade"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <def>A
slope or declivity in a manege ground down which a horse is made to
gallop, to give suppleness to his haunches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>caladenia</ent>⟦br⟧
